<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE topic PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Topic//EN" "topic.dtd">
<topic id="editing-large-documents">
  <title>Loading Large Documents</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Large documents</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>When you open a document with a file size larger than the limit configured in <xref
        href="preferences-editor-open.dita#preferences-editor-open/performance-section"
          ><uicontrol>Open</uicontrol> preferences</xref>, <ph keyref="product"/> prompts you to
      choose whether you want to optimize the loading of the document for large files or for huge
      files.</p>
    <p>
      <fig>
        <title>Large File Prompt Dialog Box</title>
        <image href="../img/large-file-dialog-box.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p>If your file has a size smaller than 300 MB, the recommended approach is <xref
        href="large-file-editor.dita#large-file-editor"><uicontrol>Optimize loading for large
          files</uicontrol></xref>. For documents that exceed 300 MB, the recommended approach is
        <xref href="huge-file-editor.dita"><uicontrol>Optimize loading for huge
        files</uicontrol></xref>.</p>
  </body>
</topic>
